node.title: Key moments in Austin's yogurt shop murders investigation
node.description: Unidentified DNA found at the scene of a 30-year-old quadruple murder recently raised hopes that this unsolved mystery might finally be solved â€” but will it crack the case?
node.content: ["Unidentified DNA found at the scene of a 30-year-old quadruple murder recently raised hopes that this unsolved mystery might finally be solved   \u2014 but will it crack the case? \"48 Hours\"' Erin Moriarty has the latest in the search for answers in \"The Yogurt Shop Murders,\" airing Saturday, February 5 at 10/9c on CBS and Paramount+.", "On December 6, 1991, a fire was reported inside an I Can't Believe It's Yogurt! shop in Austin, Texas. Once the fire was extinguished, investigators made a discovery inside the store that haunts the city to this day. \u00a0"]
